description: Infrastructure hardware and GPIO rules
globs: SolarTracker.Infrastructure/Hardware/**/*.cs, SolarTracker.Application/Interfaces/Hardware/**/*.cs
alwaysApply: false
---

# Infrastructure Hardware

- GPIO access belongs to `SolarTracker.Infrastructure`.
- Hardware abstractions belong to `SolarTracker.Application.Interfaces.Hardware`; concrete implementations belong to `SolarTracker.Infrastructure.Hardware`.
- Hardware services must remain stateless and cancellation-aware.

# Raspberry Pi Rules

- The project must support execution on Raspberry Pi hardware.
- Linear motor control must expose `MoveUpAsync` and `MoveDownAsync`.
- Hardware implementations must not contain domain orchestration or persistence logic.
- Development and non-hardware environments may use a fake actuator implementation.
